</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a conspicuous serrated area on embolar base and, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF3CCEECFE71FBE6D856387F" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[398,773,1079,1105]" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3CCEECFC3BFF4EDF763C96" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[964,1061,158,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coylei">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3CCEECFC3BFF4EDF763C96" box="[964,1061,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. coylei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the legs with metatarsi and tarsi lighter (
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF3CCEECFC7EFF12DFBF3CF3" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[897,1260,195,221]" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 15 B).
</paragraph>
